	Depp tango    
	 London, Sept. 21 (PTI): Actor Johnny Depp hates dancing, but has been forced by the director of his coming film to do a tango.       
	The 36-year-old actor had to put on his dancing shoes for Terry Gilliam, who directed him in The Imaginarium of Doctor Parnassus, reports the Daily Mirror.      
	Asked at the Toronto International Film Festival who the best dancer was, Gilliam said: I think Johnny has to do the dancing (in the film) and he hates dancing. He said: Men dont dance, and yet we get him tangoing.    
	Hunk show    
	London (PTI): Fans were in for a surprise as actors Hugh Jackman and Daniel Craig decided to drop in during Oprah Winfreys show unannounced. She was taping her show at the Central Park in New York when the actors dropped in.     
	Halle photo    
	Los Angeles (PTI): Actress Halle Berry fell for her model boyfriend Gabriel Aubry when she first saw him in a photo. The star, who has a one-year-old daughter with Aubry, confessed on The Jay Leno Show that she was smitten when she saw him standing next to a bus in the picture, reports People.
                                                                                                                                                                       
